    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm using Windows 11 and start neovim using `nvim`, so I assume it's using default Windows Terminal which can be confirmed by running `:!ver`.\n```\n:!ver\n[No write since last change]\nMicrosoft Windows [Version 10.0.22635.5170] \n```\nBut terminal output in nvim seems to be inconsistent with the default windows terminal. \nBelow are 2 examples. Can confirm that running both examples in Terminal works fine - unicode colors and color codes are displayed by default.\n\n### Unicode characters.\n\nRunning commands below result in either unicode text replaced with question marks or error running Python script.\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n:!echo тест\n:!py -c \"print('тест')\"\n```\n\nOutput:\n```\n???? \n\nTraceback (most recent call last):                                                                                        \nFile \"<string>\", line 1, in <module>                                                                                    \nFile \"C:\\software\\Python311\\Lib\\encodings\\cp1252.py\", line 19, in encode\n return codecs.charmap_encode(input,self.errors,encoding_table)[0]\n^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nUnicodeEncodeError: 'charmap' codec can't encode characters in position 0-3: character maps to <undefined>    \n```\n----\n\n### Colored output.\n```\nnvim --clean\n!echo test > xxx\n!echo new > yyy\n!git diff --color xxx yyy\n```\n\nOutput:\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a9922951-aa15-434a-9c69-f1bdc09d430c)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n 1. Output unicode characters without errors.\n 2. Output colors.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nPrints without issues. VIM - Vi IMproved 9.1 (2024 Jan 02, compiled Jan 26 2025 21:15:39)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ncmd, Microsoft Windows [Version 10.0.22635.5170]\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nIs it available on Windows?\n\n### Installation\n\nGithub Releases",
